HEADWORD: Epididymis
<hw>Ep`i*did"y*mis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/; <grk>'epi`</grk> upon + <?/ testicle.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>An oblong vermiform mass on the dorsal side of the testicle,
composed of numerous convolutions of the excretory duct of that
organ.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Ep`i*did"y*mal</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epididymitis</ent>⟦br⟧
